<section class="section is-medium tertiary relative" id="timeline">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 class="has-text-centered section-title"> Timeline &amp; Roadmap</h2>
    <div class="timeline is-centered">
      <header class="timeline-header">
        <span class="tag">2014</span>
      </header>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-marker"></div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <p class="heading">2014 - Q4</p>
          <p class="heading-alt dark-indigo">LegalThings is incorporated</p>
          <p class="muted">LegalThings is created as a spin-off of FIRM24. LegalThings provides a software suite for building documents and digital signing.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <header class="timeline-header">
        <span class="tag">2016</span>
      </header>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-marker"></div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <p class="heading">2016 - Q1</p>
          <p class="heading-alt dark-indigo">Workflow engine v1.0</p>
          <p class="muted">The LegalThings workflow engine is released. The first version powers the FIRM24 procedures for incorporations. Others clients start using the engine for digitizing the contracts as FSM (Finite State Machine) and complex signing procedures.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <header class="timeline-header">
        <span class="tag">2017</span>
      </header>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-marker"></div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <p class="heading">2017 - Q3</p>
          <p class="heading-alt dark-indigo"><a href="https://www.bitcoinwednesday.com/speakers/legally-binding-smart-contracts-legalthings-daniels-schmitz/">Hackathon winner by the Dutch Ministry of Justice</a></p>
          <p class="muted">During the blockchain hackathon organized by the Dutch Ministry of Justice and Security, we demonstrated that a whole legal procedure can be digitized as an FSM and stored on the blockchain. This got us the 1st prize in the event which included the assignment to create the first digitized legal procedures for the Dutch legislative system on the blockchain.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <header class="timeline-header">
        <span class="tag">2018</span>
      </header>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-marker"></div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <p class="heading">2018- Q1</p>
          <p class="heading-alt dark-indigo">Launch of LTO Network &amp; seed sale</p>
          <p class="muted">LegalThings becomes LTO Network. The private layer is released, depending on Waves as public layer, featuring a modified version of the workflow engine. $1.4MM was raised during the seed sale.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-marker"></div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <p class="heading">2018 - Q3</p>
          <p class="heading-alt dark-indigo">Pilot for Waste Transportation</p>
          <p class="muted">LTO launches a decentralized solution for automated permit checks in assignment of the Dutch and Belgian ministry of interiors. This marks the first time LTO Network is used in a production environment.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <header class="timeline-header">
        <span class="tag">2019</span>
      </header>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-marker"></div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <p class="heading">2019 - Q1</p>
          <p class="heading-alt dark-indigo"><a href="https://medium.com/ltonetwork/mainnet-is-live-wallet-release-2ee895af615">Mainnet launch and crowd sale</a></p>
          <p class="muted">The LTO Network mainnet is launched; a modified fork of Waves. We close the last round of token sale, raising almost $1MM from the crowd sale and $1.6MM from the private sale. LTO is listed on BitMax.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-marker"></div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <p class="heading">2019 - Q3</p>
          <p class="heading-alt dark-indigo"><a href="https://blog.ltonetwork.com/nen-lto-network-iso-standards/">NEN preferred blockchain</a></p>
          <p class="muted">LTO Network becomes the preferred blockchain of the NEN; The Royal Dutch institute for normalization and standards.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <header class="timeline-header">
        <span class="tag">2020</span>
      </header>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-marker"></div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <p class="heading">2020 - Q1</p>
          <p class="heading-alt dark-indigo"><a href="https://www.binance.com/en/support/articles/360039566471">Binance lists LTO Network</a></p>
          <p class="muted">LTO Network is selected by Binance for free listing. Initially only ERC20 and BEP2 are supported. Later LTO mainnet tokens will also be supported by Binance. LTO is also listed by LiteBit.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-marker"></div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <p class="heading">2020 - Q2</p>
          <p class="heading-alt dark-indigo"><a href="https://blog.ltonetwork.com/fillthedoc-blockchain-adoption/">fillthedoc &amp; LetsFlow</a></p>
          <p class="muted">fillthedoc is launched, a standalone product that anchors on LTO Network. The workflow engine is rebranded as LetsFlow and separated from the LTO private layer.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-marker"></div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <p class="heading">2020 - Q2</p>
          <p class="heading-alt dark-indigo"><a href="https://blog.ltonetwork.com/new-transaction-type-associations/">Associations and sponsored accounts</a></p>
          <p class="muted">The first major mainnet upgrade, adding two transaction types: associations and sponsored accounts.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-marker"></div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <p class="heading">2020 - Q2</p>
          <p class="heading-alt dark-indigo"><a href="https://blog.ltonetwork.com/foundation-supply-burning/">Governance improvement,üî• burning 50M LTO</a></p>
          <p class="muted">LTO Network burns all 50 million tokens held by the foundation, which is 11% of the total supply.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-marker"></div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <p class="heading">2020 - Q3</p>
          <p class="heading-alt dark-indigo"><a href="https://blog.ltonetwork.com/foundation-supply-burning/">Staking on Binance and BitMax</a></p>
          <p class="muted">Exchanges Binance and BitMax launch locked staking programs for LTO as alternative to staking and leasing on mainnet using a community node.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-marker"></div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <p class="heading">2020 - Q3</p>
          <p class="heading-alt dark-indigo"><a href="https://blog.ltonetwork.com/deflationary-asset-burning-defi-model/">Deflationary token economics</a></p>
          <p class="muted">With the second major mainnet update, LTO Network switches to a deflationary model. For every transaction, part of the fee is burned.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-marker"></div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <p class="heading">2020 - Q4</p>
          <p class="heading-alt dark-indigo"><a href="https://unhabitat.org/un-habitat-oict-and-lto-network-release-first-open-source-urban-land-registry-solution-for-the">United Nations land registry</a></p>
          <p class="muted">United Nations and LTO Network release world‚Äôs first open-source land registry. The land registry solution is handed to the Afghan Government by the UN Human Settlements Programme Afghanistan.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-marker"></div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <p class="heading">2020 - Q4</p>
          <p class="heading-alt dark-indigo"><a href="https://blog.ltonetwork.com/lto-network-and-vidt-datalink-merge-to-become-the-front-to-back-b2b-blockchain-solution-2/">LTOxVIDT merger</a></p>
          <p class="muted">LTO Network and VIDT Datalink join forces to become the front-to-back B2B blockchain solution. Both tokens will continue to exists and serve different purposes.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <header class="timeline-header">
        <span class="tag">2021</span>
      </header>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-marker"></div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <p class="heading">2021 - Q1</p>
          <p class="heading-alt dark-indigo">100.000 daily transactions</p>
          <p class="muted">LTO Network reaches the milestone of 100.000 daily transactions, becoming the 12th most used public blockchain according to <a href="https://coinstats.network/">Coinstats</a>.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <header class="timeline-header">
        <span class="tag">UPCOMING</span>
      </header>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-marker"></div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <p class="heading">2021 - Q1</p>
          <p class="heading-alt dark-indigo">LTO Identity platform</p>
          <p class="muted">Launch of the LTO Identity platform, supporting of Decentralized Identifiers (DIDs).</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-marker"></div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <p class="heading">2021 - Q2</p>
          <p class="heading-alt dark-indigo">Public certificate support on mainnet</p>
          <p class="muted">New transaction type on mainnet, allowing organizations to publish X.509 certificates on-chain. LTO mainnet will support addition cryptographic algorithms like EdDSA and RSA.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-marker"></div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <p class="heading">2021 - Q2</p>
          <p class="heading-alt dark-indigo">Cross-chain DIDs</p>
          <p class="muted">The identity platform will be able to generate and index DIDs of other blockchains, like Ethereum, based on the public key from an published public certificate.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-marker"></div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <p class="heading">2021 - Q3</p>
          <p class="heading-alt dark-indigo">Cross-chain associations</p>
          <p class="muted">LTO will can be used by DeFi projects to meet KYC regulations, partnering with Chainlink as oracle network.</p>
        </div>
